Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.In a large bowl, mix together the two types of flour, bicarbonate of soda and salt.Add the buttermilk and mix until a sticky dough forms.Lightly flour a work surface and tip the dough onto it.Gently roll and fold the dough a couple of times to bring the mixture together. Do not knead.Shape the dough into a ball. Flatten the ball gently with your hand. Score the dough with a deep cross dividing it into quarters. Dust the bread with flour.Place onto a baking tray lined with baking parchment and bake for 30 minutes at 200C/400F/Gas 6.  The loaf should be golden-brown.Leave to cool on a wire rack. This is best eaten on the day of baking.